(1, 2, 'Florida', 'Williamsonside', 'For Sale', 'William J. Leber Funeral Home', 'William J. Leber Funeral Home is a life celebration funeral home. The funeral planning team works around the clock to make the end-of-live service of your loved one memorable by using pictures, video, and music. When you choose a life celebration, the format can be more casual with dancing, chatting, and hobby displays. The funeral home has been around since 1998 and was designed by a local architect, John Booth. The use of natural country embellishments creates a warm venue filled with natural light and high domed ceilings. This inviting atmosphere is perfect for your family and friends to give their final goodbyes.\r\n\r\nWilliam J. Leber Funeral Home offers traditional funeral services as well, with a graveside service at the burial site and an open-casket viewing before the funeral service. Cremation services are a popular option as well, with direct cremation being the most budget-friendly option. Pair a cremation with a memorial ceremony to honor the life of your loved one with the urn on display. Or you can have a combination of a funeral and cremation by renting a casket for the funeral and getting the cremation done after the service.\r\n\r\nThe funeral home offers military honors and veteran services for the fallen hero in your family. They can help you provide proof to receive the military benefits and include special traditions in the service. The planning team is also aware of what a shock the loss of a loved one can be. Ask about the grief resources offered to help you through this difficult time.\r\n\r\nWilliam J. Leber Funeral Home is the newest and most modern funeral in the area, serving Randolph, Mendham, Succasunna, Hackettstown, Mount Olive Township, Stanhope, Netcong, Peapack, Gladstone, Tewksbury, and Long Valley. The funeral products available for purchase through the home are caskets, urns, vaults, and memorials at all price points.\r\n\r\nWilliam J. Leber Funeral Home allows for pre-planning services so that you can record your wishes for a funeral that may be years in the future. First, see the beautiful facilities yourself by visiting 15 Furnace Rd Chester, NJ 07930. Then, give them a call to start planning: (908) 879-3090.\r\n\r\nChester life celebrations\r\n\r\nChester funeral home\r\n\r\nChester funerals', 'am_1.jpg', 0, 0, NULL, '2021-09-14 11:47:32', NULL),
(2, 2, 'Florida', 'Williamsonside', 'Job Listing', 'College Steps is Hiring Peer Mentors!', 'College Steps is hiring students at the County College of Morris to serve as peer mentors for College Steps students living with social or learning challenges. Work to support fellow students with their academic and independent living goals, there\'s free specialized training and a flexible schedule.\r\n\r\nLearn More!\r\n\r\nApply Today! http://bit.ly/PeerMentorApply', '', 0, 0, NULL, '2021-08-16 11:47:32', NULL),
