(35, 101, 'District of Columbia', 'Washington DC', 'Gigs & Services', 'Top Causes of Electrical Fires And How To Prevent Them', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Electrical fires are a real concern. Electrical fires can happen anywhere from kitchens and restrooms to space heaters, light fixtures, and extension cords. In fact, according to the National Fire Protection Association, it is not uncommon for electrical fires to be on the rise. This is because&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; color: #009e13; text-decoration-line: none; font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 26.4px;\" href=\"https://watermoldfire.net/washington-dc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">there are so many potential causes of an electrical fire</a>, and oftentimes they are not preventable due to poor wiring or damaged/defective wiring in a building.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; font-size: 1.375rem; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">Check the Current State of Your Electrical System</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">First, check the current state of your home\'s electrical system. Fire hazards can arise if any part of your home\'s wiring is damaged or outdated: be sure that it meets&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; color: #009e13; text-decoration-line: none; font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 26.4px;\" href=\"https://www.nfpa.org/codes-and-standards/all-codes-and-standards/list-of-codes-and-standards/detail?code=70\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">National Electric Code</a>&nbsp;standards and is inspected regularly by a professional electrician.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Inspect the electrical cords of your appliances regularly for damage, especially if they have been dropped or crushed, or opt to call a technician from a&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; color: #009e13; text-decoration-line: none; font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 26.4px;\" href=\"https://watermoldfire.net/fire-damage-restoration\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">fire damage restoration company</a>&nbsp;to assist you with the inspection. Cords that are cracked or broken can become exposed and damaged, which may cause them to catch fire during use. Even a small nick in the insulation of a cord can expose the wires inside, causing a short circuit and fire hazard. You should immediately replace any damaged cords with new ones.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; font-size: 1.375rem; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">Overload Circuits and Improper Wiring</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Home fires from electrical problems are often caused by overloaded circuits and improper wiring. If you experience frequent electrical problems, such as blown fuses or tripped circuit breakers, it may be time to have your home\'s wiring and circuits reviewed. Electrical systems should handle a load of all attached appliances and fixtures, including air conditioners, refrigerators, and other major appliances.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; font-size: 1.375rem; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">Cordless Appliances and Extension Cords</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Corded appliances that use electrical power also pose a fire hazard if they are not used properly. Keep your appliance cords out of high-traffic areas where they may get damaged or caught on something.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Extension cords are one of the most common causes of household fires and should be used with extreme caution. Never run extension cords under carpets, where they can get damaged by furniture or vacuum cleaners. Never overload extension cords by using too many appliances at once; always unplug one appliance before plugging another in.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; font-size: 1.375rem; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">Dryers</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Inspecting and cleaning dryer vents is another way to prevent household fires from electrical problems. Dryers should be dry before they are plugged in; if not, unplug them at once when you\'re finished using them so that excess humidity cannot build up inside them. Appliances such as blenders and dishwashers use extra heat, which can cause fires in dryers. To avoid this problem, thoroughly clean the vent of your dryer and any other appliances you use that draw excessive heat.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Any work or renovations that require electricity should be done by a&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; color: #009e13; text-decoration-line: none; font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 26.4px;\" href=\"https://watermoldfire.net/home\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">licensed electrician</a>. As a last resort, if the wiring or electrical components become seriously damaged, all home occupants should leave immediately and seek shelter elsewhere until help arrives.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Turn off all appliances when not in use. This includes fridges, ovens, stoves, and ranges. Periodically check for signs of overload or overheating in appliances that have automatic control systems (like microwaves).</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Water Mold Fire Restoration of Washington DC</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">2200 Pennsylvania Ave NW</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Washington, DC 20037</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">(202) 650-0299</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; min-height: 1px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26.4px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px; color: #009e13; text-decoration-line: none; font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 26.4px;\" href=\"https://watermoldfire.net/washington-dc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://watermoldfire.net/washington-dc/</a></p>', '6153ebc383fd1_top-causes-of-electrical-fires-and-how-to-prevent-them___09172240347.jpg', 1, 1, NULL, '2021-09-29 04:29:55', '2021-09-29 05:49:23'),
