artners who provide services to Neighborhood Reporter, such as user support; marketing services; hosting; research and analytics; administration of contests and sweepstakes; sending or supporting advertising; and otherwise in connection with provision of the Service. These service providers or Partners may also share information with Neighborhood Reporter that they collect or obtain from or about you in connection with their services, and they may share such information with their subsidiaries, joint ventures or other companies under their common control.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">Some portions of the Sites may use framing or other techniques to serve content to you from our Partners, or otherwise provide content that is hosted by our Partners, while preserving the &ldquo;look and feel&rdquo; of the Neighborhood Reporter Service. Please note that the information you provide or that is collected about you in any such portion of the Sites is being provided to a third party Partner.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">In order to process a payment, Neighborhood Reporter may provide information, including your personal information, to a third party payment processor(s). Neighborhood Reporter is not responsible for any third party payment processor&rsquo;s privacy practices.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">Advertisers and other Partners may use &ldquo;cookies&rdquo; on or through the Service to collect the same types of information for the same purposes as Neighborhood Reporter. Such third parties may be able to associate information they collect in connection with the Service with other information they have about you from other sources. Please see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #007bff; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.neighborhoodreporter.com/privacy#cookies-beacons\">Cookies, Web Beacons and Similar Technologies</a>&nbsp; for more information on use of cookies by such third parties.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">We may share non-personally identifiable information, such as advertising identifiers or other information with third parties to facilitate targeted or interest-based advertising, including advertising across devices and platforms. We may also aggregate or anonymized information with third parties, such as as advertisers or other Partners.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">Our content partners may be able to use and display public content available through the Service, including content you have provided.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">In response to legal process such as a court order or subpoena or a request by law enforcement or a government agency, or as otherwise required by law.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">To other business entities in connection with the sale, assignment, merger or other transfer of all or a portion of Neighborhood Reporter&rsquo;s business to that business entity.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">In connection with any investigation, prevention or action Neighborhood Reporter may take, in our discretion, with respect to activities we believe may be illegal, or violate our&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #007bff; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.neighborhoodreporter.com/terms\">Terms of Use</a>&nbsp;or other policies, or an emergency that may pose a threat to your or another person&rsquo;s safety, or as necessary to protect Neighborhood Reporter&rsquo;s rights and property.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">We will not sell your Personal Information to any third party not affiliated with Neighborhood Reporter without your consent, except in connection with the sale or merger of Neighborhood Reporter or some or all of its assets or the division responsible for applicable services, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy. Please see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #007bff; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.neighborhoodreporter.com/privacy#annex-2\">Annex 2</a>&nbsp;for additional disclosures required under the California Consumer Privacy Act.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">We may sometimes send offers to certain users on behalf of other businesses. When we do this, we do not share your name or address with the other business. You can opt-out of receiving such offers as provided in&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #007bff; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.neighborhoodreporter.com/privacy#update-correct\">Updating and Correcting Your Information</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">If you participate in a contest or sweepstakes, or another part of the Service sponsored by a third party, the third party may obtain or collect information about you. Neighborhood Reporter does not control how any such third party uses or discloses your information. Be sure to review third party privacy policies to find out how they will collect, use and disclose your information.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">If you register with Neighborhood Reporter and create a profile, the information you provide in your profile and the content you submit, such as posts, photographs and videos, and comments, and classifieds and events you place, will be publicly displayed and published on the Service. Information and content you submit (including classifieds and events) is subject to our&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #007bff; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.neighborhoodreporter.com/terms\">Terms of Use</a>.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"cookies-beacons\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 16px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef;\">Cookies, Web Beacons, and Similar Technologies</h3>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">Neighborhood Reporter and its Partners may use browser cookies, Flash cookies, or locally shared objects (&ldquo;LSOs&rdquo;) that operate similarly to browser cookies, &ldquo;web beacons,&rdquo; clear GIFs, advertising identifiers, tags and etags, scripts and similar technologies (collectively, &ldquo;cookies&rdquo;) in connection with your use of the Service or third party websites, mobile applications or platforms. Such &ldquo;cookies&rdquo; may include unique identifiers, and may be placed on your computer&rsquo;s browser or your device, on web pages, in an email or in other locations. Neighborhood Reporter and its Partners may use &ldquo;cookies&rdquo; to recognize your device; store your preferences; track and collect information about user behavior, for example by counting the number of visitors to a web page, tracking open rates, clicks and forwards; prevent fraud; comply with legal requirements; and facilitate and enhance communication and interaction with the Service or with other websites or services. Cookies may be persistent or may be stored for a single session.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">Neighborhood Reporter, or its Partners, may also use cookies and similar technologies to customize your visit to or use of the Service, or to help enhance or improve the Service, for example by storing your password or delivering relevant advertising to you when you use the Service. We may also work with our Partners to use such technologies to help them provide advertisements to you when you visit other websites or applications, and to research and analyze how the Service is used and user response to and interaction with advertisements.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">Neighborhood Reporter may work with our Partners to synchronize unique, non-personally identifiable identifiers in order to match our identifiers with those used by our Partners. These companies may collect and use non-personally identifiable information during your visits to or use of the Service and other websites and apps. The use of cookies, web beacons and similar technologies by such Partners and advertisers is not in Neighborhood Reporter&rsquo;s control and is subject to the privacy policies of such third parties.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">By accessing or using the Service, you consent to such use of cookies and other technologies, and similar technologies that may be developed in the future, by Neighborhood Reporter and its Partners. You may be able to set your browser to disable cookies or LSOs, or to refuse certain types of cookies or warn you before accepting cookies. LSOs using Adobe Flash can be managed using Flash management tools on the&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #007bff; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.macromedia.com/support/documentation/en/flashplayer/help/settings_manager07.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Adobe website</a>. However, doing so may mean that certain parts of the Service may not work for you. Further, &ldquo;opting out&rdquo; does not prevent the display of all advertising. Some Partners may use technologies other than cookies to recognize your computer or device or to collect information about your use of the Service or other websites or services, and you may not be able to block use of such technologies. While some browsers may transmit &ldquo;do not track&rdquo; signals to websites and online services, the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) has not yet established universal standards for recognizable &ldquo;do not track&rdquo; signals, and therefore Neighborhood Reporter does not currently take any action or respond to such signals.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 12px 0px; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ebedef; font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\">Neighborhood Reporter or its Partners may use mobile Software Development Kits (&ldquo;SDKs&rdquo;) to collect information, such as your IDFA or Android Advertising ID, and other information about how your device interacts with the Service. SDKs allow app developers to enable advertising, collection of data and related services and analytics in apps. Neighborhood Reporter may use this technology to deliver, or to help Partners deliver, advertising through the Apps and other mobile applications and browsers based on information associated with your device. Depending on your device, you may be able to reset your device&rsquo;s advertising identifier by accessing the privacy settings.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\