(173, 101, '2021-09-29 04:17:48', 'District of Columbia', 'Washington DC', 'Chipotle Names Basketball Player From DC Area Athlete Ambassador', 'Arlington\'s Azzi Fudd, who played for St. John\'s High School in D.C., receives sponsorship from Chipotle as athlete ambassador.', '<hr />\r\n<p>ARLINGTON, VA &mdash; Arlington\'s Azzi Fudd, who is a freshman guard on the University of Connecticut women\'s basketball team, recently signed with Chipotle Mexican Grill to become one of the brand\'s inaugural college athlete ambassadors.</p>\r\n<p>On July 1, the NCAA adopted a new policy allowing colleges athletes to profit from their name and likenesses. Chipotle published a post on Twitter inviting fans to tag a college athlete in need who could use the company\'s sponsorship. Fudd and fellow athlete ambassador Jaiden Fields of the University of Georgia will collaborate with Chipotle during the year to promote its \"Real Food For Real Athletes\" platform. The program is designed to help athletes at all levels improve their performance by eating \"real food and real ingredients,\" according to a Chipotle release. Fudd and Field will also receive Chipotle celebrity cards, giving them access to free Chipotle food.</p>\r\n<p>A graduate of St. John\'s High School in Washington, D.C., Fudd is a three-time DC Player of the Year and two-time National Player of the Year. She also earned three gold medals as a member of USA Basketball.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><code></code></p>', '6153e8b6a9013_ap21187713773594___28160834137.jpg', 'Schools', 'article', 'active', 'district-of-columbia/washington-dc/chipotle-names-basketball-player-from-dc-area-athlete-ambassador', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2021-09-29 04:17:48', '2021-10-02 04:26:34'),
(174, 101, '2021-09-29 04:20:28', 'District of Columbia', 'Washington DC', 'DC Road Rage Shooting Suspect Arrested in Costa Rica', 'A Maryland man wanted in connection with a road rage shooting in D.C. in May was arrested on Thursday in Costa Rica, the D.C. police said.', '<div class=\"styles_HTMLContent__6IqYK\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: #111111; font-family: Merriweather, Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; word-break: break-word; padding-left: 70px; padding-right: 70px;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">WASHINGTON, DC &mdash; A Maryland man wanted in connection with a road rage shooting in D.C. in May was arrested on Thursday in Costa Rica, according to the Metropolitan Police Department.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"styles_HTMLContent__6IqYK\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: #111111; font-family: Merriweather, Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; word-break: break-word; padding-left: 70px; padding-right: 70px;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">Kenneth Miles Davis Jr., 42, of Clinton, Maryland, is going through the extradition process and upon his return to D.C. will be charged on an outstanding arrest warrant. In June, the MPD&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; color: #067638;\" href=\"https://patch.com/district-columbia/washingtondc/dc-police-identify-maserati-drive-apparent-road-rage-shooting\">issued an arrest warrant</a>&nbsp;for Davis on the charge of assault with a deadly weapon.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">The department said Thursday that its collaboration with the U.S. Marshals Service, Department of State, and Department of Homeland Security led them to Costa Rica where Davis was located.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"styles_HTMLContent__6IqYK\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: #111111; font-family: Merriweather, Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.8; word-break: break-word; padding-left: 70px; padding-right: 70px;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">Police offered a $10,000 reward for the arrest and conviction of Davis.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"r-embed\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">\r\n<div class=\"twitter-tweet twitter-tweet-rendered\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; display: flex; max-width: 550px; width: 550px;\"><iframe id=\"twitter-widget-0\" class=\"\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; width: 550px; position: static; visibility: visible; height: 922px; display: block; flex-grow: 1;\" title=\"Twitter Tweet\" src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/embed/Tweet.html?dnt=false&amp;embedId=twitter-widget-0&amp;features=eyJ0ZndfZXhwZXJpbWVudHNfY29va2llX2V4cGlyYXRpb24iOnsiYnVja2V0IjoxMjA5NjAwLCJ2ZXJzaW9uIjpudWxsfSwidGZ3X2hvcml6b25fdHdlZXRfZW1iZWRfOTU1NSI6eyJidWNrZXQiOiJodGUiLCJ2ZXJzaW9uIjpudWxsfSwidGZ3X3NwYWNlX2NhcmQiOnsiYnVja2V0Ijoib2ZmIiwidmVyc2lvbiI6bnVsbH19&amp;frame=false&amp;hideCard=false&amp;hideThread=false&amp;id=1433505806528532484&amp;lang=en&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fpatch.com%2Fdistrict-columbia%2Fwashingtondc%2Fdc-road-rage-shooting-suspect-arrested-costa-rica-police&amp;sessionId=0b75260719443c9e11af3fd74857f49433197b2d&amp;theme=light&amp;widgetsVersion=1890d59c%3A1627936082797&amp;width=550px\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" data-tweet-id=\"1433505806528532484\"></iframe></div>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">Davis was caught on surveillance video on May 19 firing a gun at a vehicle in a road rage incident in the 1600 block of Eastern Avenue NE, according to the MPD.</p>\r\n<div class=\"styles_HTMLContent__6IqYK\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; line-height: 1.8; word-break: break-word; padding-left: 70px; padding-right: 70px;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">Police said that another driver attempted to change lanes in front of Davis\'s Maserati. Video shows Davis getting out of his car and walking up to the vehicle and firing a handgun at the female driver. Police said the woman was injured and that a child riding in the car sustained cuts caused by the shattered glass when the shooting occurred. Two children, ages 5 and 11, were in the car at the time of the shooting.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">Police said Davis shot at another vehicle before leaving the area in his car.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"styles_HTMLContent__6IqYK\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; line-height: 1.8; word-break: break-word; padding-left: 70px; padding-right: 70px;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">\"This individual felt like it was necessary to use gun violence to deal with his anger,\" D.C. Police Chief Robert Contee III said at a news conference in June. \"I am here to tell him that is unacceptable in the District of Columbia.\"</p>\r\n<figure class=\"r-embed\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\">\r\n<div class=\"video-container\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px -70px; overflow: hidden; position: relative; padding-top: 314.8px; width: inherit !important;\" data-aspectratio=\"16:9\"><iframe style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; width: 699.662px; height: 314.8px; left: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QucVORKdKcc\" allowfullscreen=\"\" data-aspectratio=\"16:9\" data-originalheight=\"281\" data-originalwidth=\"500\"></iframe></div>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">RELATED:&nbsp;</strong><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; color: #067638;\" href=\"https://patch.com/district-columbia/washingtondc/dc-police-identify-maserati-drive-apparent-road-rage-shooting\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px;\">DC Police Identify Maserati Driver In Apparent Road Rage Shooting</strong></a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '6153e94652970_david___02153725549.jpg', 'Crime & Safety', 'article', 'draft', 'district-of-columbia/washington-dc/dc-road-rage-shooting-suspect-arrested-in-costa-rica', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2021-09-29 04:20:28', '2021-09-29 04:20:28'),
(175, 101, '2021-09-29 04:21:36', 'District Of Columbia', 'Washington Dc', '', '', 'UBS advisor Keith Apton named to the Forbes/SHOOK Top 250 Wealth Advisors list\r\n\r\nWashington, D.C., September 27, 2021 – UBS Wealth Management USA announced today that Keith Apton, a Financial Advisor in the firm’s Washington, D.C. office, has been named to the Forbes/SHOOK Research Top 250 Wealth Advisors list for 2021.\r\n\r\n“We’re thrilled that Keith received this well-deserved recognition on such a prestigious list,” said Ellen Pierce, D.C. and Mid-Atlantic Market Head at UBS Wealth Management USA. “Throughout his career, Keith has achieved success by dedicating his full attention to helping his clients achieve their financial goals. His inclusion on this year’s list is a direct reflection of his hard work.”\r\n\r\nKeith has more than 19 years of experience in the financial services industry, with an extensive background in corporate finance. As the founding partner of his team, The Capital ESOP Group at UBS, Keith’s helps small-to-middle-market business owners with sell-side advisory solutions and post-sale financial planning, to include holistic wealth management and tax and estate planning strategies. Prior to joining UBS in 2009, Keith was a Financial Advisor at Morgan Stanley, where he was an integral member of the team handling all of the firm’s Employee Stock Ownership Program (“ESOP”) transactions.\r\n\r\nKeith is a member of both the National Center for Employee Ownership and the finance committee for The ESOP Association. After becoming a Certified Exit Planning Advisor® (CEPA®) in 2018, he became an instructor for the Exit Planning Institute. Keith lives in Washington, D.C. with his wife and two daughters.\r\n\r\nThe sixth annual Forbes/SHOOK Research Top 250 Wealth Advisors list recognizes the country\'s top financial advisors who represent the future of the wealth management industry.\r\n\r\nFor the full list and further information visit: https://www.forbes.com/top-wealth-advisors.', '6153e9d002c2e_1200px-Facebook_Logo_(2019).png', '', 'neighbour', 'active', '', 1, 2, NULL, NULL, '2021-09-29 04:21:36', '2021-10-05 10:17:05'),
