(177, 1, '2021-10-01 20:52:10', 'New Jersey', 'Mount Olive Township', 'Guts and Glory:', 'Area Olympians Reflect on Tokyo Games', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">After a yearlong delay due to the COVID-19 pandemic, Team USA headed to Tokyo to take care of business and with Team USA were members of the Morris, Essex, and Passaic counties communities. We recently caught up with some of those athletes who called the Olympic Village in Tokyo home for the two-week games.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">On the streets, the water, and the bike, Morgan Pearson represented the US on the Triathlon Team. Pearson, age 27, hails from the New Vernon area of Harding Township. A Delbarton Grad, Pearson grew up as a competitive swimmer and transitioned into running during his time in high school. In 2017, Pearson was recruited by USA Triathlon, and he competed his first ever triathlon in 2018.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Pearson automatically qualified to Tokyo after competing in the Yokohama Triathlon.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve always dreamed of competing at the world class level. You want to be the best at what you do. As a runner, I</span></p>\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_76671\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: inline; margin: 2px 0px 0px 10px; float: right; background: #f1f1f1; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; max-width: 98%; color: #333333; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; width: 300px;\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-76671\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; outline: 0px; color: #337ab7; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-scaled.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-76671\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto !important; border: 0px none; vertical-align: middle; display: block; line-height: 0; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px;\" src=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-300x282.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-300x282.jpg 300w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-1024x964.jpg 1024w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-768x723.jpg 768w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-150x141.jpg 150w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-600x565.jpg 600w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-1536x1446.jpg 1536w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-2048x1928.jpg 2048w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-570x536.jpg 570w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-701x660.jpg 701w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Francesca-Russo-1067x1004.jpg 1067w\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"282\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-76671\" class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 4px;\">Credit to Francesca Russo. Francesca Russo takes in the Olympic Rings</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">knew I could be good. I thought I could be a national champion, maybe one of the best runners in the country, but I never thought I could win a medal in running. But with Triathlon, I always felt that I could go to the Olympics and win a medal,&rdquo; Pearson shares.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Pearson was frustrated with his individual performance at the games but had a chance at redemption during the mixed team relay competition. He finally achieved his podium glory and brought home the silver medal to Harding Township.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;I think an Olympic medal means a lot to any athlete. The overwhelming feeling was that we won the silver medal and there was so much excitement and joy. But there is always that small percentage of you that was wishing for more. You dream of gold but if you leave with a medal, you still leave extremely happy,&rdquo; Pearson said.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Pearson is currently enjoying some time with family but plans to take it one day at a time in terms of committing to training for Paris 2024.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_76669\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: inline; margin: 2px 10px 0px 0px; float: left; background: #f1f1f1; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; max-width: 98%; color: #333333; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; width: 225px;\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-76669\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; outline: 0px; color: #337ab7; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Keturah-Orji-in-Olympic-Village.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-76669\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto !important; border: 0px none; vertical-align: middle; display: block; line-height: 0; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px;\" src=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Keturah-Orji-in-Olympic-Village-225x300.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\" srcset=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Keturah-Orji-in-Olympic-Village-225x300.jpg 225w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Keturah-Orji-in-Olympic-Village-150x200.jpg 150w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Keturah-Orji-in-Olympic-Village.jpg 543w\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-76669\" class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 4px;\">Credit to Keturah Orji. Keturah Orji in the Olympic Village</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;I always say that people talk about sacrifices that an athlete has to make to train. My sacrifice is spending time away from my family. The training and workouts are things that I really enjoy. I have some more races I want to do this year and right now, I want to go for Paris, but I want to soak in these emotions right now from Tokyo,&rdquo; Pearson shared.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Meanwhile over at the Tokyo Olympic Stadium, Mount Olive&rsquo;s Keturah Orji was getting set to compete in her second Olympic Games in the triple jump. At the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio, Orji placed just off the podium in fourth place. With high hopes for Tokyo, Orji qualified to the triple jump final in fifth position. During the final, Orji placed seventh.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;I was disappointed with my performance for sure. In 2016, I placed fourth which is actually the highest finish by an American woman in the triple jump. My goal was really to win a medal and be the first American woman to medal in the triple jump. It would have been great to create that history, but things don&rsquo;t always go as we plan,&rdquo; Orji said.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">While this was Orji&rsquo;s second Olympics, she says it felt different due to the COVID protocols, but she was honored to represent the US and Mount Olive.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;It&rsquo;s always an honor when I get the chance to represent my country. The US Olympic Team is one of the hardest</span></p>\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_76670\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: inline; margin: 2px 0px 0px 10px; float: right; background: #f1f1f1; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; max-width: 98%; color: #333333; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; width: 245px;\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-76670\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; outline: 0px; color: #337ab7; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Jackie-Dubrovich.jpeg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-76670\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto !important; border: 0px none; vertical-align: middle; display: block; line-height: 0; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px;\" src=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Jackie-Dubrovich-245x300.jpeg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 245px) 100vw, 245px\" srcset=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Jackie-Dubrovich-245x300.jpeg 245w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Jackie-Dubrovich-150x184.jpeg 150w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Jackie-Dubrovich-570x698.jpeg 570w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Jackie-Dubrovich.jpeg 591w\" alt=\"\" width=\"245\" height=\"300\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-76670\" class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 4px;\">Credit to Jackie Dubrovich. Jackie stands proudly with the US Flag in the Olympic Village</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">teams to make in the world. Despite the fact that I didn&rsquo;t perform as well as I wanted to at my second Olympics, I know that it was extremely difficult to make the team and that I should always just be grateful to be there,&rdquo; Orji says.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Even though Orji didn&rsquo;t bring home hardware from the games, she has already set her sights on the Paris 2024 summer games, summing up that she&rsquo;s still got much more to prove.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;There&rsquo;s still many more Olympics and World Championships to come along in my career,&rdquo; Orji shared.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">When the world was focused on the Ariake Gymnastics Center, Caldwell&rsquo;s Elizaveta Pletneva was ready to represent the US with the rhythmic gymnastics team. Pletneva has been doing rhythmic gymnastics for as long as she can remember.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;I was four years old and my parents knew they wanted to put me in a sport. We tried everything from soccer, ballroom dance, swimming, etc. We ended up finding a rhythmic gymnastics coach that wasn&rsquo;t too far away from where we lived. They took me there and I fell in love with it and stuck with it ever since,&rdquo; Pletneva said.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_76668\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; display: inline; margin: 2px 10px 0px 0px; float: left; background: #f1f1f1; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; max-width: 98%; color: #333333; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; width: 300px;\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-76668\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; outline: 0px; color: #337ab7; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-76668\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; max-width: 100%; height: auto !important; border: 0px none; vertical-align: middle; display: block; line-height: 0; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px;\" src=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-300x238.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-300x238.jpg 300w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-1024x812.jpg 1024w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-768x609.jpg 768w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-150x119.jpg 150w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-600x476.jpg 600w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-1536x1218.jpg 1536w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-2048x1623.jpg 2048w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-570x452.jpg 570w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-701x556.jpg 701w, https://www.mypaperonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Elizaveta-Pletneva-1067x846.jpg 1067w\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"238\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a>\r\n<figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-76668\" class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 12px; line-height: 20px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 4px;\">Credit to Elizaveta Pletneva. Elizaveta poses with the Olympic Rings inside the Ariake Gymnastics Center</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Rhythmic gymnastics is comprised of different events; the balls, ribbons, clubs, and hoops. Rhythmic gymnasts can compete in all four events or as part of a rhythmic gymnastics team. Pletneva and the rhythmic gymnastics team competed in the qualification round but did not earn a high enough ranking to advance to the finals.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;My team and I are very happy with how we did. Rhythmic gymnastics isn&rsquo;t really known in America. We don&rsquo;t bring home a lot of medals, but we have improved a lot over the past few decades. If we keep going like this, we&rsquo;ll get stronger and stronger. We performed two clean routines and we had no expectations of winning a medal going into it. There was no crazy pressure of being expected to bring home a medal so we really just enjoyed it,&rdquo; Pletneva said.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Overall, Pletneva&rsquo;s experiences in Tokyo were once in a lifetime.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;It was amazing overall. I&rsquo;ve been dreaming about it since I was a little girl. To just actually be there and experience every moment of it was absolutely incredible. We were there for about a week and we got to do everything. To see other athletes, eat in the dining hall, seeing all the shops and salons in the village, taking the bus and seeing all the arenas, to actually competing. I don&rsquo;t think there was one moment that I didn&rsquo;t enjoy and a lot of it still feels like a dream come true,&rdquo; Pletneva shared.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Finally, Riverdale&rsquo;s Jackie Dubrovich and Wayne&rsquo;s Francesca Russo were preparing to fence at the Makuhari Messe. The Tokyo games were the first Olympics for both Dubrovich and Russo.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Russo became involved in fencing when she was nine with her thirteen year old sister. The sabre fencer then went to a fencing summer camp at Wayne Valley High School and that&rsquo;s where she met her very first fencing coach, Mark Trudnos.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Russo recalls the moment of being named to the team.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;It was a crazy moment when I made it onto the Olympic team. It was a dream come true. I was very excited for this all to happen, but it was in such an uncertain time that there was a lot on my mind,&rdquo; Russo shares.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">When she arrived in Tokyo, she tried her best to take it all in. From the Olympic Village to pin trading to meeting athletes from all over the world, Russo looks back at her Olympic experience with pride.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;I wouldn&rsquo;t trade my experience for anything. We were on cloud nine and it was the coolest experience of my life. To see all the countries and to watch all the athletes wander around in their countries gear, it felt like an out of this world experience. I had to remind myself every day that I was actually in the Olympic Village,&rdquo; Russo said with a laugh.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">During competition, Russo fenced as part of the Women&rsquo;s Sabre team. After losing to France in the quarterfinal, the sabre team had to fight for places. They successfully fenced China for the 5-6 place, but ultimately lost to Japan, ending their Olympic journey with a sixth-place finish.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;I&rsquo;m really proud of my teammates more than anything. We&rsquo;ve had a really rough couple of years with injuries. I&rsquo;m really proud of just being a part of that team, but of course, my individual performance left me frustrated. I feel like I had one opportunity to showcase my talents and it didn&rsquo;t go as planned. But, I also see the larger picture which is that I got to compete on the Olympic stage and nobody can take that away from me,&rdquo; Russo says.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Dubrovich, a foil fencer, first tried gymnastics and dance as a little girl. Being tall for her age, gymnastics and dance were not the easiest of sports to continue with. Her cousin, a fencer for Fair Lawn High School, talked to Dubrovich&rsquo;s parents about fencing and it piqued Jackie&rsquo;s interest.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;I took casual lessons when I was eight. But then, I started doing well and that was my main motivator. I did well on the local level, state level, and regional level. As I&rsquo;ve grown older, I really started to appreciate fencing for what it is and not just the medals and the winning. There&rsquo;s so many intricacies and nuances to this sport and I really started to love it for what it was and not just the winning component of it,&rdquo; Dubrovich recalls about her start.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Dubrovich was named to the Olympic team following her final qualification competition in Doha, Qatar in April 2020.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;After Doha, I was officially named to the team. I finished second in the country and that was the most incredible moment. It was a huge sigh of relief because it had been so stressful for me. It had already been stressful but then you add COVID on top of that and all those uncertainties, it was a culmination of all the hard work and the years of sacrifice that I&rsquo;ve had to make,&rdquo; Dubrovich says.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Ultimately, Dubrovich competed in Tokyo as an individual competitor and as part of the foil fencing team. She placed 21</span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">st</span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;overall individually, and followed up her individual performance with a fourth place finish in the team competition. Although she did not bring home a medal, she talks about her Olympic experience with nothing but pride.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&ldquo;It&rsquo;s hard to put into words because ever since I was eight years old, all of these 19 years of sacrifices that I&rsquo;ve made, and all the hard work, the blood, sweat, and tears that has gone into this, to be able to represent the United States of America is an incredible experience. I&rsquo;m so proud to represent the United States, I&rsquo;m so proud to be an Olympian and I&rsquo;m so proud to represent a sport that has given so much to me all these years,&rdquo; Dubrovich said.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: georgia, \'palatino linotype\', palatino, \'times new roman\', times, serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">For more post-Olympic content, visit&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; outline: 0px; color: #337ab7; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.olympics.com/\">www.olympics.com</a><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">.&nbsp;</span></p>', '615774d33c9d6_Morgan-Pearson-701x467.jpg', 'Community Corner', 'article', 'active', 'new-jersey/mount-olive-township/guts-and-glory:', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2021-10-01 20:52:10', '2021-10-01 20:52:10'),
